## üèóÔ∏è Architecture

The `routine-workflow` follows a clean `src/` layout with modular components.

```text
src/routine_workflow/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ __init__.py
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ banner.py           # CLI Banner & Art
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ cli.py              # Entry point & Argument Parsing
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config.py           # Configuration Dataclass
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ defaults.py         # Default Settings
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lock.py             # Concurrency Control
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ runner.py           # Workflow Orchestrator
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ steps/              # Modular Step Definitions
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step1.py        # Delete Dumps
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step2.py        # Reformat Code
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step2_5.py      # Pytest Runner
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step3.py        # Clean Caches
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step3_5.py      # Security Scan
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step4.py        # Backup
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step5.py        # Create Dumps
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ step6.py        # Git Operations
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ step6_5.py      # Dependency Audit
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils.py            # Helpers
```

**Core Flow:**
1. **Config Loading**: Loads defaults, env vars, and CLI args into a `WorkflowConfig` object.
2. **Lock Acquisition**: Ensures only one instance runs via `lock.py`.
3. **Step Resolution**: Maps requested aliases (e.g., `audit`) to step modules (e.g., `step6_5.py`).
4. **Execution**: The `WorkflowRunner` executes steps sequentially, handling logging and errors.
5. **Report**: Generates a summary of the run.

